SwiftUI layouts are declarative and powerful. By combining ZStack, VStack, and HStack, you can create complex and responsive user interfaces with minimal code.

In this tutorial, we will explore:
- How to use VStack for vertical alignment.
- How to use HStack for horizontal alignment.
- How to use ZStack for layering views on top of each other.
- Best practices for nesting stacks to create sophisticated layouts.
